    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="590" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d590">
                <head>No. 590.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to
                            Mr. <persName type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-03-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 29,
                            1880</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 71.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                        67, transmitting the result of your presentation to His Majesty’s Government
                        of the considerations contained in the circular instruction of August last,
                        touching the prevention of an emigration to this country from foreign parts
                        of persons intending to join the Mormon community in Utah, and in reply to
                        request that you will express to His Majesty’s Government the appreciation
                        of the Government of the United States of the action taken by it in the
                        direction referred to.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN HAY,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                        Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
